Cooperative weather and hundreds of firefighters helped beat back flames Sunday that had threatened hundreds of homes near a Southern California dam .
Evacuation orders were lifted just before dawn for about 300 homes in an area along the border of Norco and Corona , about 35 miles southeast of downtown Los Angeles .
By midday , fire officials said they had contained 25 per cent of the fire , which had grown to 1.5 square miles .
